l":2},{"id":1705202,"age":45,"year":"1558","julianDay":2290108,"title":"Act of Uniformity","description":"The Act of Uniformity was passed by the Parliament of England and required all people to go to church once a week. The consequence of not attending church was a fine of 12 pence, which was a considerable amount for a poor person.","jurisdictionLevel":2},{"id":1705205,"age":56,"year":"1569","julianDay":2294126,"title":"State Lottery","description":"A State Lottery was recorded in 1569. The tickets were sold at St. Paul's Cathedral in London.","jurisdictionLevel":2},{"id":1705206,"age":58,"year":"1571","julianDay":2294856,"title":"The Royal Exchange is Organized","description":"The Royal Exchange was organized in January 1571 by Sir Thomas Gresham. Gresham is known as the father of English banking.","jurisdictionLevel":2},{"id":1705210,"age":87,"year":"1600","julianDay":2305448,"title":"The Honourable East India Company","description":"The Honourable East India Company, a British joint-stock company, was established in 1600 for trade in the Indian Ocean region. At its height, the British East India Company had a private army which was twice the size of the British Army, ruled large sections of India, and revenues in the millions.","url":"https://www.historic-uk.com/HistoryUK/HistoryofEngland/The-East-India-Company/","urlTitle":"Historic UK - The East India Company","jurisdictionLevel":2}],"lifeSummary":"When John Ingorsol was born about 1513, in Sidmouth, Devon, England, United Kingdom, his father, John Ingersoll, was 24 and his mother, Rose Ingersoll, was 18. He had at least 1 son with Rose Taley Saley. He died on 18 August 1617, in Derby, Derbyshire, England, at the age of 105."},"et":{"about 1513–18 August 1617":"umbes 1513–18. august 1617","1513–1617":"1513–1617","1515–1617":"1515–1617","1537–1617":"1537–1617","1490–1540":"1490–1540","1496–Female":"1496–Surnud","1571":"1571","1490":"1490","1569":"1569","1558":"1558","18 August 1617":"18. august 1617","1513":"1